North Korea completely refuses unilateral disarmament without confidence
The Minister for Foreign Affairs of North Korea stated to the United Nations on Saturday that the maintenance of sanctions was unabated by the country's mistrust in the United States, which in such circumstances would have refused to give up its nuclear weapons unilaterally.
