The NTS, responsible for the care of over 270 historic buildings, 38 important gardens and 76,000 hectares of land in the country, takes bats very seriously.
Ten qualified experts regularly conduct investigations, inspect truffles and sometimes carry out rescues.
The organization has even established the first reserve of Scotland for bats only at the estate of Thrave, in the region of Dumfries and Galloway, which houses eight of the ten species of bats of Scotland.
