In front of the United Nations General Assembly, the Minister for Foreign Affairs Walid al-Moualem said that the country's conditions are improving.
"Today the situation on the territory is more stable and secure thanks to the progress made in the fight against terrorism," he said.
The government continues to recover the areas destroyed by terrorists to restore normality.
Now there are all the conditions for the voluntary return of refugees to the country that have had to leave because of terrorism and unilateral economic measures that have affected their daily lives and their livelihood.
According to the United Nations estimate, more than 5.5 million Syrians have abandoned the country since the beginning of the war in 2011.
Another six million who still live in Syria need humanitarian aid.
Al-Moualem said that the Syrian regime would gladly accept assistance to rebuild the devastated country.
But he stressed that he would not accept any conditional or conditional aid from those countries that supported the insurrection.
